What is Docker Swarm?
Docker Swarm is a native clustering and orchestration tool for Docker that allows you to manage multiple Docker machines (nodes) as a single system.
“Swarm = many Docker servers working together as ONE system”

🧠 Why Swarm exists (problem it solves)
Without Swarm::-
-----------------
You run containers on one machine
If machine fails → app goes down ❌
Scaling is manual ❌

With Swarm:
---------------
Multiple machines (nodes)
Auto failover
Auto load balancing
Easy scaling
-------------------------------------------------------------------
How Docker Swarm Works
Client Request
      ↓
Swarm Manager
      ↓
Distributes load
      ↓
Worker Nodes (Containers run here)
=================================================================
1. What Swarm is doing in your case?
When you stop 1 container in Swarm:
3 replicas → 2 running → Swarm brings it back to 3
👉 This is called: ✔ Self-healing (NOT autoscaling)

Swarm ensures:
Desired state = 3 replicas
If one fails → it replaces it
🔥 2. What Swarm DOES NOT do

Swarm does NOT:
❌ Increase replicas based on CPU load
❌ Scale based on traffic
❌ Use advanced scheduling rules
❌ Do predictive scaling
❌ Handle complex distributed systems well
